A resolution to 8 test tasks given by Rebilly

A 2D side-view platformer prototype where the player controls a wizard who can place water bubbles in the air by clicking. When you click within range, a bubble flies to that exact position and hovers there, acting as a temporary platform. The player can stand and jump on settled bubbles to reach higher areas. Bubbles have a limited lifetime of about 5 seconds, visualized by a shrinking health bar above each one. As they near death, they shrink and wobble to warn the player. Crucially, standing on a bubble drains its life much fasteraround 3 times the normal ratewhich creates pressure to keep moving rather than camping on a single platform. The placement range is limited to a radius around the player, shown as a dashed circle. The goal is to reach an elevated golden platform by building a temporary staircase of bubbles before they pop
